TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Impact of Economic Reform on the Performance of Chinese State Enterprises, 1980–1989
AU  - Li, Wei
Y1  - 1997/10/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/262106
DO  - 10.1086/262106
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 1080
EP  - 1106
VL  - 105
IS  - 5
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The effectiveness of China's incremental industrial reform between 1980 and 1980 is investigated using a panel data set of 272 state enterprises. This paper applies a method that measures marginal products of factors and changes in total factor productivity (TFP) by comparing actual changes in output to actual changes in inputs and in the institutional environment. This paper finds that there were marked improvements in the marginal productivity of factors and in TFP between 1980 and 1989. More important, the evidence shows that over 87 percent of the TFP growth was attributable to improved incentives, intensified product market competitioni, and improved factor allocation.
AB  - The effectiveness of China's incremental industrial reform between 1980 and 1980 is investigated using a panel data set of 272 state enterprises. This paper applies a method that measures marginal products of factors and changes in total factor productivity (TFP) by comparing actual changes in output to actual changes in inputs and in the institutional environment. This paper finds that there were marked improvements in the marginal productivity of factors and in TFP between 1980 and 1989. More important, the evidence shows that over 87 percent of the TFP growth was attributable to improved incentives, intensified product market competitioni, and improved factor allocation.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/262106
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/262106
Y2  - 2024/03/22
